OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,FHouseholds are facing further cost
OL,8,Fpressures on their food bills due to
OL,9,Fdegraded soils and climate volatility,
OL,10,Faccording to campaigners.
OL,12,FThe Save Soil movement said it had
OL,13,Festimated that a typical household
OL,14,Fcould potentially end up paying
OL,15,Fhundreds of pounds more per year.
OL,17,FIt said that degraded soils are slower
OL,18,Fto recover, so droughts, heatwaves and
OL,19,Ffloods cause larger yield losses and
OL,20,Fsharper price swings.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
