OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782019145
OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,FCampaigners argued that restoring soil
OL,8,Fhealth is among the most cost-
OL,9,Feffective hedges against future
OL,10,Fshocks, with low-income families who
OL,11,Fspend more of their budget on food
OL,12,Fparticularly at risk in terms of the
OL,13,Fprice impact.
OL,15,FEarlier in June, the Met Office said
OL,16,Fthat the El Nino climate pattern could
OL,17,Fincrease the chances of milder, wetter
OL,18,Fand windier weather in the UK during
OL,19,Fautumn and early winter.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
