OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782019145
OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,FEl Nino is a warming of the Pacific
OL,8,FOcean near the equator that affects
OL,9,Fweather patterns around the world.
OL,11,FConcerns have also been raised that UK
OL,12,Ffood imports could be coming under
OL,13,Ffurther pressure from climate impacts
OL,14,Famid speculation that 2027 could
OL,15,Fbecome the hottest year on record.
OL,17,FEl Nino typically takes place
OL,18,Firregularly every two to seven years
OL,19,Fand usually lasts nine to 12 months.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
