OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,FPraveena Sridhar, chief policy and
OL,8,Fscience officer of Save Soil, said
OL,9,Fstaples such as potatoes, bread and
OL,10,Fvegetables could be particularly
OL,11,Fexposed in terms of the pressure on
OL,12,Ffamily budgets, adding: "Prices are
OL,13,Fdriven by energy, labour and global
OL,14,Fmarkets, but soil decides how hard
OL,15,Feach shock lands.
OL,17,F"Healthy soil holds water through a
OL,18,Fdrought and structure through a flood,
OL,19,Fso yields hold and prices steady."
