OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,FSave Soil is calling for a legally
OL,8,Fbinding soil health target, a national
OL,9,Fsoil-monitoring scheme and funding for
OL,10,Ffarmer advice and training.
OL,12,FOffice for National Statistics (ONS)
OL,13,Ffigures released last week showed UK
OL,14,Finflation unexpectedly flatlined last
OL,15,Fmonth as a slowdown in food price
OL,16,Frises offset pressure from air fares.
OL,18,FThe Office for National Statistics
OL,19,F(ONS) said Consumer Prices Index (CPI)
OL,20,Finflation was recorded at 2.8% in May,
OL,21,Fthe same rate as in April.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
