OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,FFood and drink inflation eased to 2.2%
OL,8,Ffrom 3% in April, falling to its
OL,9,Flowest level since December 2024.
OL,11,FA Government spokesperson said: "We
OL,12,Fare taking a range of actions to keep
OL,13,Fprices down for households, including
OL,14,Fthe cost of the weekly shop.
OL,26,@sD@aOU
