OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782019145
OL,3,CHousehold food bills 'risk pressure
OL,4,Cfrom degraded soil and climate
OL,5,Cvolatility'
OL,7,F"We've committed to maintaining
OL,8,Fdomestic food production by investing
OL,9,Fbillions in the development of new
OL,10,Ftechnology to increase yields, develop
OL,11,Fclimate resilient crops and help
OL,12,Ffarmers produce more food; and we're
OL,13,Fincreasing our water supply by
OL,14,Fbuilding new reservoirs for the first
OL,15,Ftime in 30 years."
OL,17,FThe spokesperson said the Government
OL,18,Fwill be launching "the 25-year farming
OL,19,Froad map with specific measures to
OL,20,Fboost soil health and support our
OL,21,Ffarmers in a changing climate".
